Home / News Business / Economy / September job figures point to slowing economy A crew works Thursday to relocate water main valves on the 800 block of Nicollet Mall in downtown Minneapolis. Construction companies shed 1,700 jobs in September, according to the Minnesota Department of Employment and Economic Development. Staff photo: Bill Klotz September job figures point to slowing economy By: Karlee Weinmann October 16, 2015 0 A shrinking labor force dragged the unemployment rate to 3.8 percent.
